Bezel is a free developer tool for Apple\'ae Watch\'99 developers who are running their apps in the iOS Simulator. It shows a window that looks like an Apple Watch and projects the contents of the Simulator\'92s watch window into it so that you can see what your app will look like in the context of a device frame surrounding it (the amount of extra black margin that it will have, etc.).\
\
Also, Bezel by default scales the simulator down to a size such that the watch screen should be closer to real-life (it will still be bigger on most desktop/laptop screens due to their DPI, however). This is particularly nice on a Retina display, as in that case, you get a high-resolution version of the watch UI where one retina pixel is showing what one pixel will show on the watch screen (the Simulator, on this kind of screen, is zoomed up to 200%).\
\
